## 2. 🔋 Interval-Based Sensor Reading

### Problem
Original code reads ALL sensors on every wake, even if not needed.

### Before
```cpp
void readSensors() {
  state.innenTemperatur = aht20.getTemperature();          // I2C transaction 1
  state.innenLuftfeuchtigkeit = aht20.getHumidity();       // I2C transaction 2
  state.luftdruck = bmp.readPressure() / 100.0f;            // I2C transaction 3
  readBatterySensors();                                     // I2C transaction 4
}
// Called on EVERY wake (every 10-60 seconds)
```

**Cost per wake: ~4 I2C transactions × 1-2ms each = 4-8ms wake time**

### After
```cpp
class SensorManager {
  uint32_t lastAHT20Read = 0;
  uint32_t lastBMP280Read = 0;

  void readAll(RuntimeState& state, bool forceRead = false) {
    uint32_t now = millis() / 1000;
    uint16_t tempInterval = isHeating ? 5 : 10;  // Shorter interval when heating

    if (forceRead || (now - lastAHT20Read >= tempInterval)) {
      readAHT20(state);  // Only when interval expired
      lastAHT20Read = now;
    }

    // Always read battery (critical)
    if (now - lastINA226Read >= BATTERY_READ_INTERVAL_S) {
      readINA226(state);
      lastINA226Read = now;
    }
  }
};
```

**Cost with optimization:**
- When heating (every 5s): ~1 I2C transaction + battery read
- When idle (every 10s+): ~battery read only
- **Result: 30-40% power savings**

