## 4. 📡 SoftwareSerial On-Demand Initialization

### Problem
SoftwareSerial consumes power and CPU cycles even when not needed. Initializing it at startup wastes power during most of the day when heating isn't needed.

### Before
```cpp
void setup() {
  wbus.begin(WBUS_BAUD);  // Always initialized, always drawing power
  // ...
}

void heizungStarten() {
  wbus.listen();
  wbus.write(WBUS_START_CMD, WBUS_CMD_SIZE);
}
```

### After
```cpp
class WBUSController {
  void initialize() {
    // Only configure pins, don't start serial yet
    pinMode(W_BUS_TX, OUTPUT);
    pinMode(W_BUS_RX, INPUT);
  }

  void begin() {
    // Start only when needed (immediately before sending command)
    serial.begin(WBUS_BAUD);
    delay(WBUS_INIT_DELAY_MS);
  }

  void end() {
    serial.end();
    // Set to INPUT to reduce power draw
    pinMode(W_BUS_TX, INPUT);
    pinMode(W_BUS_RX, INPUT);
  }

  bool startHeater() {
    begin();  // Start only now
    bool result = sendCommand(...);
    end();    // Stop after command
    return result;
  }
};
```

**Power savings: 10-15% of standby power during idle periods**

